Robert 'Bob' Burns Jr died late Friday in a single-vehicle crash near Cartersville, Georgia . 
  He was a founding member of the Southern hard rock band Lynyrd Skynyrd . 
  Burns' vehicle went off the road just before midnight as it approached a curve . 
  He is about 125 miles away from where Duane Allman died in a 1971 motorcycle crash . 
  Burns played on the song Free Bird dedicated to the Allman Brothers guitarist . 
 